Group ride (no-drop) Angry Catfish Wednesday social ride. Instagram. Discord. Website.

When: Wednesday Oct 1, 2025 rolling at 6:00 pm. First Wednesday of each month during cold weather months.

Start: Angry Catfish Bicycle Finish: Venn Brewing Company

Distance: ~15 miles. Pace: 12-13 mph.

Bring lights, dress for the weather. Led by: Alex & Adam

Some additional considerations as weather gets colder:
- Dress for the weather, we will ride even when the temperature gets real low. Layers, pogies, and toe warmers are your friends. Ask friends how they layer, experiment and enjoy the thrill of winter riding.
- Ride based on your comfort level - rides will be in the dark and can be icy/snowy. Studded and/or fat tires encouraged in the depths of winter. Lights required.

Led by: Alex & Adam.

See Discord link for ride updates.
items.location: Angry Catfish Bicycle, 2900 E 42nd St, Minneapolis, MN 55406, USA

items.summary: Behind Bars Como Conservatory Group Ride
items.description:
Group ride (no-drop) Behind Bars Como Conservatory ride. Instagram.

When: Sunday Feb 15, 2026 12:00 PM. Meet at 12:00 PM, roll at 12:15 PM

Start: Behind Bars Bicycle Shop Finish: The Briar 

Mid-ride stop: Como Park Zoo & Conservatory

Distance: ~15 miles. Pace: typically 10-12 mph. 

Mid ride stop at Como Zoo Conservatory. We will spend an hour or so enjoying everything the conservatory has to offer.

Leaders: @sirbikesalot365

Things you may need:

- Bike Lock, Helmet, Water, Proper clothing (bring layers)

*Check the weather*

**Group Rides are a safe space for everyone, respect everyone!**
items.location: Behind Bars Bicycle Shop

items.description:
Gathering and Group ride (no-drop) FTWNB cyclist meet-up. Instagram.

When: Sunday Feb 22, 2026 10:00 AM.

Where: FRGMNT Coffee - St. Anthony Main

Who’s this for: FTW (anyone but cis-men). See this resource from Grease Rag defining FTW.

Are you NOT a cis-man? Do you ride bikes? Any bike? Show up and meet others who also ride bikes!!!


I am looking to create a regularly meeting group to ride bikes in DIFFERENT ways <3 I love exploring dirt as much as I love rush hour pavement. And im tired of doing it alone. maybe you want other endurance riders to train with, maybe you are tired of mountain biking alone, maybe you are new to the city. Maybe you need to vent about being a gender minority in cycling!


You DONT need to ride your bike to this. Weather is barrier, just say hi! Will there be a ride? Yes! Do I know where? Not yet!


TIP your barista.

NO TRANSPHOBIA, NO RACISM, NO TRUMPISM, NO ASSHOLE BEHAVIOUR TOLERATED. Also an anti-ICE space.
items.location: FRGMNT Coffee - St. Anthony Main, 43 SE Main St, Minneapolis, MN 55414, USA
